<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,770,827,853]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Key to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1805" box="[287,428,827,853]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pompilinae">Pompilinae</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[467,650,827,853]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" box="[151,244,892,916]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Females</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
1 Pronotum with collar not well differentiated from disc; streptaulus absent medially and collar on nearly same plane as disc (
<figureCitation box="[232,311,957,978]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1345,1368]" captionTargetBox="[249,1337,193,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-113@45.[249,1338,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 8. A. Psorthaspis hispaniolae: head and front femora, front-lateral view, ♀. B, G–H, K. Anoplius fulgidus, lateral view: B. head and anterior mesosoma, ♀; G.postnotum, ♀; H. front basitarsus, ♀; K. metasoma, ♂. C. Drepanaporus collaris: front femora, lateral view, ♀. D–E. Epysiron conterminous cressoni: ♀: D. postnotum, dorsal view; E. propodeum, lateral view. F.Aporinellus medianus: propodeum, lateral view, ♀. I–J. Anoplius amethystinus amethystinus: lateral view: I. front basitarsus, ♀. J. metasoma, ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251744/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
), or if on lower plane streptaulus absent altogether; pronotum longer than mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1262,957,978]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1345,1368]" captionTargetBox="[249,1337,193,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-113@45.[249,1338,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 8. A. Psorthaspis hispaniolae: head and front femora, front-lateral view, ♀. B, G–H, K. Anoplius fulgidus, lateral view: B. head and anterior mesosoma, ♀; G.postnotum, ♀; H. front basitarsus, ♀; K. metasoma, ♂. C. Drepanaporus collaris: front femora, lateral view, ♀. D–E. Epysiron conterminous cressoni: ♀: D. postnotum, dorsal view; E. propodeum, lateral view. F.Aporinellus medianus: propodeum, lateral view, ♀. I–J. Anoplius amethystinus amethystinus: lateral view: I. front basitarsus, ♀. J. metasoma, ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251744/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); eyes sometimes wholly covered with short setae.......................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
- Pronotum with collar separated from disc by complete streptaulus; disc sloping upward strongly from collar; pronotum shorter than mesonotum along midline, or at least not notably longer (
<figureCitation box="[822,897,1045,1066]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1345,1368]" captionTargetBox="[249,1337,193,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-113@45.[249,1338,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 8. A. Psorthaspis hispaniolae: head and front femora, front-lateral view, ♀. B, G–H, K. Anoplius fulgidus, lateral view: B. head and anterior mesosoma, ♀; G.postnotum, ♀; H. front basitarsus, ♀; K. metasoma, ♂. C. Drepanaporus collaris: front femora, lateral view, ♀. D–E. Epysiron conterminous cressoni: ♀: D. postnotum, dorsal view; E. propodeum, lateral view. F.Aporinellus medianus: propodeum, lateral view, ♀. I–J. Anoplius amethystinus amethystinus: lateral view: I. front basitarsus, ♀. J. metasoma, ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251744/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
); eyes never setose........................... 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
2 Fore wing with three radial sectors; front femora not swollen (
<figureCitation box="[828,906,1074,1095]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1345,1368]" captionTargetBox="[249,1337,193,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-113@45.[249,1338,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 8. A. Psorthaspis hispaniolae: head and front femora, front-lateral view, ♀. B, G–H, K. Anoplius fulgidus, lateral view: B. head and anterior mesosoma, ♀; G.postnotum, ♀; H. front basitarsus, ♀; K. metasoma, ♂. C. Drepanaporus collaris: front femora, lateral view, ♀. D–E. Epysiron conterminous cressoni: ♀: D. postnotum, dorsal view; E. propodeum, lateral view. F.Aporinellus medianus: propodeum, lateral view, ♀. I–J. Anoplius amethystinus amethystinus: lateral view: I. front basitarsus, ♀. J. metasoma, ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251744/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); integument black with bluish tomentum (
<taxonomicName authority="Banks" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Psorthaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1323,1436,1074,1095]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Psorthaspis</emphasis>
Banks
</taxonomicName>
)............................................................................................. 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
- Fore wing with two radial sectors; front femora usually swollen; integument black with red markings (
<figureCitation box="[1203,1276,1133,1154]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1345,1368]" captionTargetBox="[249,1337,193,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-113@45.[249,1338,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 8. A. Psorthaspis hispaniolae: head and front femora, front-lateral view, ♀. B, G–H, K. Anoplius fulgidus, lateral view: B. head and anterior mesosoma, ♀; G.postnotum, ♀; H. front basitarsus, ♀; K. metasoma, ♂. C. Drepanaporus collaris: front femora, lateral view, ♀. D–E. Epysiron conterminous cressoni: ♀: D. postnotum, dorsal view; E. propodeum, lateral view. F.Aporinellus medianus: propodeum, lateral view, ♀. I–J. Anoplius amethystinus amethystinus: lateral view: I. front basitarsus, ♀. J. metasoma, ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251744/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
) (
<taxonomicName authority="Bradley" authorityName="Bradley" authorityYear="1944" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Drepanaporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1297,1436,1133,1154]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Drepanaporus</emphasis>
Bradley
</taxonomicName>
)........................................................................................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" box="[151,1436,1191,1213]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1191,1213]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
3 Fore wing translucent, with a broad, dark maculation covering the first radial 2 cell............ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1855" box="[1177,1357,1192,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Psorthaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="naomi">
<emphasis box="[1177,1357,1192,1213]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Psorthaspis naomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1369,1429,1191,1212]" country="Bermuda" name="Smith's" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Smith</collectingRegion>
)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" box="[151,1436,1221,1242]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1221,1242]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
- Fore wing uniformly dark.................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Bradley" authorityName="Bradley" authorityYear="1944" box="[1123,1436,1221,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Psorthaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispaniolae">
<emphasis box="[1123,1354,1221,1242]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Psorthaspis hispaniolae</emphasis>
Bradley
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" box="[151,1420,1250,1271]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead box="[151,1420,1250,1271]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
4 Eyes setose; 
<emphasis box="[348,409,1250,1271]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2m-cu</emphasis>
vein of fore wing interstitial or slightly distal 
<emphasis box="[851,897,1250,1271]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2r-m</emphasis>
vein (
<figureCitation box="[958,1032,1250,1271]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1349,1372]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,193,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-111@39.[210,1376,193,1328]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 2. A. Pepsis marginata: hind and fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. B. Auplopus bellus: propodeum, lateral view, ♂.C. Drepanaporus collaris: hind and fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. D. Anoplius fulgidus: fore and hind wing, dorsal view, ♀. E. Tachypompilus ferrugineus: fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. F. Anoplius americanus ambiguus: fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. G. Anoplius hispaniolae: fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. H. Drepanaporus antillarum: fore wing, ♀. I. Dipogon marlowei sp. nov.: fore wing, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251734/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
) … 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bradley)" authorityName="Waichert &amp; Rodriguez &amp; Von Dohlen &amp; Pitts" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Bradley" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[1076,1420,1250,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Drepanaporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antillarum">
<emphasis box="[1076,1322,1250,1271]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Drepanaporus antillarum</emphasis>
(Bradley)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
- Eyes with or without vestigial setae; 
<emphasis box="[579,639,1280,1301]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2m-cu</emphasis>
vein of fore wing not interstitial with 
<emphasis box="[1005,1051,1280,1301]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2r-m</emphasis>
vein (
<figureCitation box="[1111,1186,1279,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1349,1372]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,193,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-111@39.[210,1376,193,1328]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 2. A. Pepsis marginata: hind and fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. B. Auplopus bellus: propodeum, lateral view, ♂.C. Drepanaporus collaris: hind and fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. D. Anoplius fulgidus: fore and hind wing, dorsal view, ♀. E. Tachypompilus ferrugineus: fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. F. Anoplius americanus ambiguus: fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. G. Anoplius hispaniolae: fore wing, dorsal view, ♀. H. Drepanaporus antillarum: fore wing, ♀. I. Dipogon marlowei sp. nov.: fore wing, ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251734/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
).............................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cresson)" baseAuthorityName="Cresson" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1118,1436,1309,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Drepanaporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis box="[1118,1336,1309,1330]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Drepanaporus collaris</emphasis>
(Cresson)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
5 Postnotum arcuately broadened on each side of median line, then constricted again opposite to propodeal spiracles (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1410,1338,1359]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1345,1368]" captionTargetBox="[249,1337,193,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-113@45.[249,1338,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 8. A. Psorthaspis hispaniolae: head and front femora, front-lateral view, ♀. B, G–H, K. Anoplius fulgidus, lateral view: B. head and anterior mesosoma, ♀; G.postnotum, ♀; H. front basitarsus, ♀; K. metasoma, ♂. C. Drepanaporus collaris: front femora, lateral view, ♀. D–E. Epysiron conterminous cressoni: ♀: D. postnotum, dorsal view; E. propodeum, lateral view. F.Aporinellus medianus: propodeum, lateral view, ♀. I–J. Anoplius amethystinus amethystinus: lateral view: I. front basitarsus, ♀. J. metasoma, ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251744/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
). .................................................................................................... 6
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" box="[151,1436,1397,1418]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1397,1418]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
- Postnotum transverse band with nearly parallel margins, or broadened at midline (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1086,1397,1418]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1345,1368]" captionTargetBox="[249,1337,193,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-113@45.[249,1338,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 8. A. Psorthaspis hispaniolae: head and front femora, front-lateral view, ♀. B, G–H, K. Anoplius fulgidus, lateral view: B. head and anterior mesosoma, ♀; G.postnotum, ♀; H. front basitarsus, ♀; K. metasoma, ♂. C. Drepanaporus collaris: front femora, lateral view, ♀. D–E. Epysiron conterminous cressoni: ♀: D. postnotum, dorsal view; E. propodeum, lateral view. F.Aporinellus medianus: propodeum, lateral view, ♀. I–J. Anoplius amethystinus amethystinus: lateral view: I. front basitarsus, ♀. J. metasoma, ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251744/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 8G</figureCitation>
)........................... 7
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
6 Metasomal tergum l, and usually parts of propodeum and mesosoma, bearing scale-like pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1307,1426,1447]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1345,1368]" captionTargetBox="[249,1337,193,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-113@45.[249,1338,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 8. A. Psorthaspis hispaniolae: head and front femora, front-lateral view, ♀. B, G–H, K. Anoplius fulgidus, lateral view: B. head and anterior mesosoma, ♀; G.postnotum, ♀; H. front basitarsus, ♀; K. metasoma, ♂. C. Drepanaporus collaris: front femora, lateral view, ♀. D–E. Epysiron conterminous cressoni: ♀: D. postnotum, dorsal view; E. propodeum, lateral view. F.Aporinellus medianus: propodeum, lateral view, ♀. I–J. Anoplius amethystinus amethystinus: lateral view: I. front basitarsus, ♀. J. metasoma, ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5251744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5251744/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
); integument black on mesosoma and metasoma........................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dewitz)" baseAuthorityName="Dewitz" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1049,1436,1455,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Episyron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="conterminus" subSpecies="cressoni">
<emphasis box="[1049,1345,1456,1477]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Episyron conterminus cressoni</emphasis>
(Dewitz)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,892,2034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<keyLead pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
- Body without scale-like pubescence; integument black with yellow markings on mesosoma, and dark brown with yellow stripes on metasoma....................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[1095,1435,1514,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Poecilopompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixtus">
<emphasis box="[1095,1325,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Poecilopompilus mixtus</emphasis>
